51. Comitio. The Comitium (meeting-place) was an open , space railed off from the north-west partos the Forum and used for the debates of the oldest Comitia or Assembly. ‘The Comitium was chosen by Boni (the Italian archaeologist) as the most appropriate place t'or exploring the archaeological strata of Rome, and examining the traces of the people's life layer upon layer in the little area where so much of it eentred. He was able to reach 23 strata one above another between the uppermost pavement and the virgin clay of the sub-soil' (E. Burton-Brown, Recent Excavations in the Forum, p. 87).
